sentence:
He had imagined it, there was no other explanation; 
imagined it, because he had been thinking of his dead 
headmaster.

With a leap of pleasure, Harry recognized his father; 
his untidy black hair stuck up at the back like 
Harry’s, and he too wore glasses.

But Master Regulus had proper pride; 
he knew what was due to the name of Black and the 
dignity of his pure blood.

He knew at once that he had done the right thing; 
though he appeared to be standing in water, his 
shoes, feet, and robes remained quite dry.

Ron was breathing heavily: His 
eyes were no longer red at all, but their normal blue; 
they were also wet.

He supposed he ought to be glad of it; 
anyone he came into contact with was in danger, 
Xenophilius’s attitude proved that.

“All right,” breathed Hermione, as the broken printing 
press blocking the top of the stairs began to tremble; 
Xenophilius was feet away from them.

“There 
was nothing fancy on there, as far as I could see; 
maybe a few scratches.

He had forgotten, lost track; 
he could not now remember whose wands these were; 
he seemed to remember wrenching them out of 
someone’s hand.

Scurrying, echoing footsteps were growing louder 
from behind the door leading to the dormitories: 
Luna’s spell had woken Ravenclaws sleeping above.

Generations of students had failed to find the diadem; 
that suggested that it was not in Ravenclaw Tower — 
but if not there, where?

“We’re gonna be rewarded,” said Crabbe: His voice 
was surprisingly soft for such an enormous person; 
Harry had hardly ever heard him speak before.

Thicknesse had fallen 
to the ground with tiny spikes erupting all over him; 
he seemed to be turning into some form of sea urchin.

With a gasp, Harry pulled back and opened his eyes; 
at the same moment his ears were assaulted with the 
screeches and cries, the smashes and bangs of battle.

A swarm of dementors was gliding amongst the trees; 
he could feel their chill, and he was not sure he would 
be able to pass safely through it.
